Author-Name: Virgiliu Midrigan
Author-Name: Daniel Yi Xu
Title: Finance and Misallocation: Evidence from Plant-Level Data
Abstract: We use producer-level data to evaluate the role of financial frictions
in determining total factor productivity (TFP). We study a model
of establishment dynamics in which financial frictions reduce TFP
through two channels. First, finance frictions distort entry and
technology adoption decisions. Second, finance frictions generate
dispersion in the returns to capital across existing producers and thus
productivity losses from misallocation. Parameterizations of our model
consistent with the data imply fairly small losses from misallocation,
but potentially sizable losses from inefficiently low levels of entry and
technology adoption.
